reviews.review_text:
another winner Another winner for Hunter.
Very good sound from a very good show!!
this sounds MIGHTY fine! Thanks to Hunter Seamons for making my matrix dreams come true!

Guitar Separation on Chinacat It is rare to hear such clearly distinct guitars. Through my headphones they sound like they are in different channels. Quite a sonic thrill! Outstanding sound quality. There was a time when I was on a tropical island and the second set of this show was all I had to listen to. I just recently became aware of the work of Hunter Seamons (and others), am very impressed and enjoying listening to their results. One more round of thanks!!

Phil JAM! Right at about 6:21 Phil just kicks the jam into overdrive - the link below goes deeper into this theme that was played during this period. This whole show is amazing - the MLB jam in CC>IKYR is sublime <3

http://deadessays.blogspot.com/2018/06/the-proto-solomon-jazz-jam.html

Wonderful Summer Dead Set 1: Very mellow Half Step to kick things off with a Sugaree following suit in third slot. China > Rider is a delight toward the end of the set. 
Set 2 : You're here for it so buckle in. 25 minute Playing to kick it off that finds all kinds of dimensions as it rolls along. Truly a thing of beauty. Solid standards through Loose Lucy and then the MASSIVE Truckin' > Other One > Wharf Rat at a total of 41 minutes over which you find nirvana. Really quality sound here, fun '73 Dead that I will absolutely revisit.
